A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Housing and Community Development – Housing Counseling
3 FOR the purpose of requiring a recipient of certain funding from the Department of
4 Housing and Community Development to offer housing counseling services to certain
5 prospective residents; and generally relating to housing counseling services.
6 BY adding to
7 Article – Housing and Community Development
8 Section 2–304
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Housing and Community Development
14 2–304.
15 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
16 INDICATED.
17 (2) “APPROVED HOUSING COUNSELING AGENCY” MEANS AN
18 ORGANIZATION THAT IS APPROVED BY THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND
19 URBAN DEVELOPMENT TO PROVIDE HOUSING COUNSELING SERVICES DIRECTLY OR
20 THROUGH AFFILIATES OR BRANCHES.
21 (3) “HOUSING COUNSELING” MEANS COUNSELOR–TO–CLIENT
22 ASSISTANCE THAT ADDRESSES UNIQUE FINANCIAL CIRCUMSTANCES OR HOUSING
