2 HOUSE BILL 1302
1 ISSUES AND FOCUSES ON WAYS OF OVERCOMING SPECIFIC OBSTACLES TO
2 ACHIEVING A HOUSING GOAL.
3 (B) AS A CONDITION ON THE RECEIPT OF FUNDING FROM THE
4 DEPARTMENT FOR ANY PROJECT TO CONSTRUCT, ACQUIRE, OR REHABILITATE
5 RESIDENTIAL PROPERTY FOR USE AS HOUSING, A FUNDING RECIPIENT SHALL
6 AGREE TO OFFER HOUSING COUNSELING SERVICES TO PROSPECTIVE RESIDENTS.
7 (C) HOUSING COUNSELING SERVICES OFFERED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF
8 THIS SECTION SHALL BE PROVIDED BY HOUSING COUNSELORS CERTIFIED BY THE
9 U.S. DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT AND EMPLOYED BY AN
10 APPROVED HOUSING COUNSELING AGENCY.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2025.

